<div type="edition" xml:lang="tam-Latn" rendition="class:tamil maturity:vernacular">

<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">svasti śrī</hi> kopparakecaripaṉ<hi rend="grantha">nma</hi>kku yāṇṭu
<lb n="2"/>12 Āvatu kuṉṟakkūṟṟattu<hi rend="grantha">brahmade</hi>yam ciṟu
<lb n="3"/>paḻuvūr<hi rend="grantha">mahāde</hi>varkku Aṭikaḷ paḻuveṭṭaraiyar
<lb n="4"/>kumaraṉ maturā<unclear>n</unclear>takaṉeṉ mātevaṭikaḷuṅ ku
<lb n="5"/>ṉṟakūṟattu mutukuṭi Irukku virakali Araṅka<unclear>nu</unclear>m kilāccu <g type="kaḻañcu"/> virakali Araṅkaṉ<note>These two words are added on the pilaster, between lines 4 and 5.</note>
<lb n="6"/>paṭa avaṉec cātti vaitta nontāviḷakku Onṟu O
<lb n="7"/>ru viḷak<unclear>ke</unclear>riya vaicca Āṭu toṇṇūṟuṅ koṇṭu nicatam
<lb n="8"/>nārāyatāl Uḻakkum Iravum paka<unclear>lu</unclear>m E
<lb n="9"/>riya vaiytta cantirātittaval |
<lb n="10"/>Itu pan<hi rend="grantha">māheśvara rakṣai </hi>||
</p>

</div>

<div type="apparatus">

</div>

<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 12th year of Kōpparakesarivarman. To Mahādeva of Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> in Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, I Aṭikaḷ Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar Kumaraṉ Maturāntakaṉ; Mātevaṭikaḷ and Vīrakali Araṅkaṉ who stays (<foreign>irukku</foreign> &gt; <foreign>irukkum</foreign>) in Mutukuṭi of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam having been angry [at each other] <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kilāccu</foreign></supplied>, Vīrakali Araṅkaṉ fell <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṭa</foreign></supplied>; on behalf <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cātti</foreign></supplied> of he <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>avaṉē</foreign></supplied>, [I] gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> one perpetual lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nontāviḷakku</foreign></supplied>; to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> one lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>oru onṟu viḷakku</foreign></supplied> [I] gave (<foreign>vaicca</foreign> &gt; <foreign>vaitta</foreign>) ninety <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>toṇṇūṟum</foreign></supplied> goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>āṭu</foreign></supplied>; with <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>koṇṭu</foreign></supplied> [them], one whole <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uḻakkum</foreign></supplied> by the <foreign>nārāyam</foreign> [measure] every day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicatam</foreign></supplied> to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> night and day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iravum pakalum</foreign></supplied> will be placed (<foreign>vaiytta</foreign> &gt; <foreign>vaitta</foreign>), as long as the sun and the moon endure. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras. </p></div>

